# Dark mode (class strategy)

Root toggles the `dark` class via `ThemeProvider` (`src/hooks/ThemeProvider.tsx`). Tailwind uses `@custom-variant dark` in `src/main/index.css`.

## Required

When adding or editing UI in `src/pages/` or `src/components/`:

- Every **background, text, border, shadow, hover, focus** style needs a matching **`dark:`** utility.
- Do not ship light-only colors that break contrast in dark theme.
- Prefer project palette: surfaces `#18191C` / `#1E2022` / `#2F3134`; text `#A0A5AC` / `#E0E2E5`; accent `#3285FF` or `blue-400`.
- Match existing transitions where used, e.g. `transition-colors duration-[750ms]`.

## Examples

```tsx
// Good
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900 border-gray-200 dark:bg-[#18191C] dark:text-[#E0E2E5] dark:border-[#2F3134]">

// Bad — no dark counterpart
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900">
```

Theme-invariant assets (e.g. brand logo) may omit `dark:`.

